==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[άντίδοτον]]'', "given against", from ''[[άντί]]'', "against" (confer Latin ''[[ante]]'', "before") + ''[[διδοναι]]'', "to give". Compare with Latin ''[[antidotum]]'' and French '''antidote'''.  See English "[[dose]]".

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæn.tə.dot/

===Noun===
# A remedy to counteract the effects of poison, or of anything noxious taken into the stomach;&mdash;used with  against, for, or to; as, an antidote against, for, or to, poison.
# Whatever tends to prevent mischievous effects, or to counteract evil which something else might produce.
